President Obama released a statement praising Senator Jay Rockefeller for his decades-long commitment to improving the lives of working families in West Virginia. Rockefeller's legacy includes advocating for better schools, safer working conditions for miners, greater retirement benefits for seniors, and the promotion of new industries in the state. The President also recognized Rockefeller's efforts in healthcare reform, ensuring that no American would face financial ruin due to illness. President Obama expressed gratitude to Senator Rockefeller for his lifetime of service and expressed his intention to continue working with him in the future.